ration that are difficult in a concept document.</span></p><br />\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">Awaiting management review of two drafts of the Integrated Lifecycle Management framework, and the Mission Needs Statement and Charter for the PPM Tool Implementation.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p><br />\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">Struggled with implementation of Google Mail (along with everyone else in WO500 &amp; state IT operations). Switch generated hundreds of emails (I did X in Outlook...how do I do that in Google?). &nbsp;Approaches are substantially different in some ways, e.g. everything is \"search\" oriented in Google&hellip; You don\'t sort the inbox by originator, you search for all emails from that person.</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p><br />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p><br />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"label\">Accomplishments:</td>\n    <td><p>Attended Application and Data Assessment Tool training for FDCCI. &nbsp; ADAT surveys are run on all applications on all servers to determine appropriateness of moving the app to the cloud. &nbsp;It has been a topic of intereste and confusion for months, and is still not totally clear.</p><br />\r\n<p>Also attended the other Google Training course. &nbsp;Pretty generic course, doesn\'t cover the look and feel of the DOI application.</p></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"label\">Meetings and Presentations:</td>\n    <td><p>The weekly Federal Data Center Consolidation Initiative conference call was uneventful.</p><br />\r\n<p>ADAT training was helpful, I think...more than a dozen people from BLM offices responsible for running ADAT surveys were in attendance, including Mike Smith of 570/580 who will handle WO server reports</p></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"label\">Issues or Problems:</td>\n    <td><p>None</p></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"label\">Items that need the attention of the COTR:</td>\n    <td><p>N/A</p></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tfoot>\n    <tr>\n      <td>&nbsp;</td>\n      <td>                                                <a href=\"/statusreport/list\" class=\"positiveaction\" title=\"Status Reports List\"><img src=\"/images/arrow_undo.png\" />Status Reports List</a>\n                </td>\n    </tr>\n  </tfoot>\n</table>\n</body></html>\";s:26:\"list_query_stringtimesheet\";a:3:{s:10:\"controller\";s:9:\"timesheet\";s:6:\"action\";s:4:\"list\";s:6:\"module\";s:7:\"default\";}}'),
