ded were accepted by the team but Public Affairs requested that the \"specific tasks\" be revised.&nbsp; I will work with Al\'Tariq to revise the Next Steps.<br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Al&rsquo;Tariq to discuss GPI prior to his meeting with Kim on 12/13/11.<span>&nbsp; </span>We discussed status and what is needed from 300.<span>&nbsp; </span>After the meeting with Kim, he stated that she was pleased with our support for the Investment.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Reviewed GPI status with Beth on 12/13/11.<span>&nbsp; </span>Provided feedback regarding ITIB requirements.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Requested timeline for documents to be submitted to ITIB for review in regards to GPI on 12/14/11.<span>&nbsp; </span>Al&rsquo;Tariq stated that they needed to be ready a week before ITIB meeting.<span>&nbsp; </span>At this time, there is no clarification on whether these are provided to CPIC.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Fred to review gate reviews and participating personnel within SLM on 12/13/11.<span>&nbsp; </span>We discussed best fits within BLM. Drafted email for Al&rsquo;Tariq to provide to CPIC regarding feedback on SLM on 12/14/11. Drafted an IM designating WO 570 as the PMO.<span>&nbsp; </span>Submitted the draft IM to Al&rsquo;Tariq on 12/15/11. Review SLM Role Definitions with Fred on 12/15/11.&nbsp; Provided feedback to Fred on 12/15/11. Reviewed updated SLM Role Definitions on 12/16/11.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Discussed templates and modifications with Mr. Lewis and Fred on 12/15/11. We noted that templates could be modified for projects.&nbsp; I provided Mr. Lewis with the Planning WBS on 12/15/11.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Other</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Attended &lsquo;All Hands&rsquo; meeting with WO 500 &ndash; All day meeting on 12/14/11.<span>&nbsp; </span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Social Media</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Revised New Media Strategy.<span> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Met  with Al\'Tariq and the Team Leads at 2pm on 12/16/11.<br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Reviewed GPI status with Beth on 12/13/11.<span>&nbsp; </span>Provided feedback regarding ITIB requirements.&nbsp; Updated GPI Project Plan.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span></span>Submitted the draft IM to Al&rsquo;Tariq on  12/15/11. Review SLM Role Definitions with Fred.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Other</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Attended &lsquo;All Hands&rsquo; meeting with WO 500 &ndash; All day meeting on 12/14/11.<span>&nbsp; </span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Social Media</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Al&rsquo;Tariq to discuss Social Media on 12/12/11.<span>&nbsp; </span>Reviewed  next steps portion and revised them. Submitted revised Next Steps to  Al&rsquo;Tariq 12/13/11 for review.&nbsp;<span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Met  with Al\'Tariq and the Team Leads at 2pm on 12/16/11.&nbsp; We reviewed the  Problem Statement provided by Alexanfra and the Next Steps.&nbsp; Arteallia  provided feedback regarding the Problem Statement and will work with  Alexandra to update it.&nbsp; I will work with Al\'Tariq to revise the  Next Steps.<br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Al&rsquo;Tariq to discuss GPI prior to his meeting with Kim on 12/13/11.<span>&nbsp; </span>We discussed status and what is needed from 300.<span>&nbsp; </span>After the meeting with Kim, he stated that she was pleased with our support for the Investment.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Reviewed GPI status with Beth on 12/13/11.<span>&nbsp; </span>Provided feedback regarding ITIB requirements.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Fred to review gate reviews and participating personnel within SLM on 12/13/11.<span>&nbsp; </span>We  discussed best fits within BLM. Drafted email for Al&rsquo;Tariq to provide  to CPIC regarding feedback on SLM on 12/14/11. Drafted an IM designating  WO 570 as the PMO.<span>&nbsp; </span>Submitted the draft IM to Al&rsquo;Tariq on  12/15/11.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Other</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Attended &lsquo;All Hands&rsquo; meeting with WO 500 &ndash; All day meeting on 12/14/11.<span>&nbsp; </span></p>',	'<p>na</p>',	'<p>na</p>',	2,	4,	'2011-12-15 23:18:48',	3,	'2011-12-23 22:04:20'),
(7,	6,	1,	1,	'2011-12-16',	'<ul>\r\n<li>Worked on revising the SLM IM for implementation</li>\r\n<li>Updated the SLM timeline for implementation</li>\r\n<li>Discuss the Section 508 Evaluation form with Mrs. Laura Bell</li>\r\n<li>Provided the DOI Section 508 Evaluation form to Mrs. Laura Bell</li>\r\n<li>Worked on finalizing the SLM IM for review</li>\r\n<li>Worked with Lauren Clapp to draft a Note to Review for the SLM IM that has to be submitted for review</li>\r\n<li>Worked on defining the SLM Roles for Ms. Levine from a previous meeting. &nbsp;Worked on defining: Business Project Manager, Technical Project Manager, Operational Project Manager</li>\r\n<li>Reviewed WO-300 Roles and responsibilities that was submitted by John Broderick</li>\r\n<li>Helped Naomi draft an email to CPIC regarding the status of them reviewing the SLM documenation</li>\r\n<li>Worked on making some additional changes to the SLM handbook regarding the role and responsibilities of CPIC</li>\r\n</ul>',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"background-image: url(../../../images/body_bg.jpeg); background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: 1.2em; height: 100%; outline-width: 2px !important; outline-style: solid !important; outline-color: rgba(254, 192, 26, 0.699219) !important; outline-offset: 1px !important; background-repeat: repeat no-repeat; margin: 8px;\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Completed and submitted an updated draft of the SLM IM for implementation to Mr. Samuels</li>\r\n<li>Completed and submitted an updated draft of the SLM timeline for implementation to Mr. Samuels</li>\r\n<li>Provided a copy of the DOI Section 508 Evaluation form to Mrs. Laura Bell to keep in their document repository</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.2em;\">Completed and submitted the updated draft SLM IM for review</span></li>\r\n<li>Completed and submitted a draft Note to Review for the SLM IM that has to be submitted for review to Lauren</li>\r\n<li>Completed and submitted the draft definitions of SLM Roles for Ms. Levine from a previous meeting. Submitted definitions for: Business Project Manager, Technical Project Manager, Operational Project Manager (change to: IRM Analyst)</li>\r\n<li>Provided my feedback regarding the WO-300 Roles and responsibilities submitted by John Broderick</li>\r\n<li>Submitted the draft email I help Naomi draft to CPIC regarding the status of them reviewing the SLM documenation</li>\r\n<li>Completed making changes to the SLM handbook regarding the role and responsibilities of CPIC </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<ul>\r\n<li>Had a brief meeting with Laura Bell regarding the Section 508 Evaluation form. 12-13-11. &nbsp;Discuss Section 508 role in the SLM process and provide Mrs. Bell a Section 508 Evaluation template since they did not have one. &nbsp;The template will be used to perform the required actions that they are required to perform.</li>\r\n<li>Had a meeting Naomi to review the GeoComm project documents. 12-14-11. &nbsp;Discussed some changes to the templates she was currently working on for the GeoComm project. &nbsp;Looked at whether the changes would have any serious impact on the overall document. &nbsp;She also recommend adding a section for functional requirements to the template that would make it easier for the business to fill out.</li>\r\n<li>Had a meeting with Naomi to assist in review the roles and responibilities in the SLM handbook. 12-15-11. &nbsp;We met to re-review the roles and responsibilities of all the supporting divisions and made some changes based on our discussion with CPIC. &nbsp;We are also going to make some suggestions to Mr. Samuels regarding adding CPIC to other phases in the SLM process for checks and balances. &nbsp;CPIC should be reviewing/performing actions in just about every phase. &nbsp;Currently CPIC noted they only need to be in 2 phases (Initiation &amp; Requirements Analysis)</li>\r\n<li>Brief meeting with Mr. Samuels regarding the SLM Roles definitions. 12-15-11. &nbsp;Met to discuss the roles Ms. Levine wanted us to define: Business Project Manager, Technical Project Manager, and Operations Project Manager. &nbsp;We discuss these different areas and I suggested we change the Operations Project Manager to Business &amp; Technology Analyst. &nbsp;After discussing Mr. Samuels decided it needed to be changed and wanted it changed to IRM Analyst.</li>\r\n</ul>',	'<p>None at this time</p>',	'<p>None at this time</p>',	2,	4,	'2011-12-19 15:35:31',	6,	'2011-12-20 23:32:49'),
(8,	3,	2,	1,	'2011-12-23',	'<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Kayla on 12/19/11 and brought her up to speed on the status of the New Media Strategy.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq, Artellia and Kayla to discuss current Strategy and updates that Artellia provided on 12/20/11.&nbsp; Al\'Tariq stated that we did not want ot include the addition of roles and responsibilities within the Strategy Document.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq, Kayla and Alexandra to discuss the Problem Statement on 12/20/11.&nbsp; We discussed revisions and how to include it in the Strategy document.</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed Alexandras Problem Statement on 12/20/11 and discussed incorporation of this into the Strategy with Al\'Tariq.</p>\r\n<p>Updated the New Media Strategy and provided it to Al\'Tariq for review on 12/21/11.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Discussed the status of ITIB items with Beth on 12/21/11. I noted that we still needed to know the amount of funding that was being requested for the Investment.</p>\r\n<p>Provided an updated of the Investments status to John on 12/22/11.</p>\r\n<p>Began putting together the ITIB presentation for review on 12/22/11 and 12/23/11.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq and Fred on 12/22/11 to discuss the concerns from the NOC regarding SLM.&nbsp; Al\'Tariq agreed that the process did incorporate agile projects but requested that we specificaly call that out.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed email repsonse to the NOC with Fred on 12/23/11.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Other</strong></p>\r\n<p>Provided Brian with response to Support Systems Team questions that were provided.</p>',	'<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Kayla on 12/19/11 and brought her up to speed on the status of the New Media Strategy.</p>\r\n<p>Updated the New Media Strategy and provided it to Al\'Tariq for review on 12/21/11.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Discussed  the status of ITIB items with Beth on 12/21/11. I noted that we still  needed to know the amount of funding that was being requested for the  Investment.</p>\r\n<p>Provided an updated of the Investments status to John on 12/22/11.</p>\r\n<p>Began putting together the ITIB presentation for review on 12/22/11 and 12/23/11.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Other</strong></p>\r\n<p>Provided Brian with response to Support Systems Team questions that were provided.</p>',	'<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Kayla on 12/19/11 and brought her up to speed on the status of the New Media Strategy.</p>\r\n<p>Met  with Al\'Tariq, Artellia and Kayla to discuss current Strategy and  updates that Artellia provided on 12/20/11.&nbsp; Al\'Tariq stated that we did  not want ot include the addition of roles and responsibilities within  the Strategy Document.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq, Kayla and Alexandra to  discuss the Problem Statement on 12/20/11.&nbsp; We discussed revisions and  how to include it in the Strategy document.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met  with Al\'Tariq and Fred on 12/22/11 to discuss the concerns from the NOC  regarding SLM.&nbsp; Al\'Tariq agreed that the process did incorporate agile  projects but requested that we specificaly call that out.&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>na</p>',	'<p>na</p>',	2,	4,	'2011-12-23 19:39:56',	NULL,	'2011-12-23 22:05:56'),
(9,	6,	1,	1,	'2011-12-23',	'<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Reviewed and worked on making revisions to the SLM IM for implementation.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Reviewed several GeoComm project documents for Naomi.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; background-color: #fafafa; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Had discussion with Mr. Samuels and Naomi regarding the NOC comments on the SLM</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; background-color: #fafafa; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Provided my feedback and comments for the new Support Process\\Systems Team I am assigned to</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; background-color: #fafafa; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Provided Naomi with the ITIB presentation template</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in;\">Had several email communications with the NOC regarding SLM</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in;\">Working on the Acquisition Strategy template. &nbsp;Need to discuss changes with IT Acquisitions.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0in;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: #fafafa; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">Completed and submitted the      revisions of the SLM IM for implementation to Mr. Samuels and Lauren</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: #fafafa; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">Make contact with Gail at the NOC to start the discuss of the issues the NOC has with current version of the SLM. &nbsp;Will be setting up a meeting after the holidays to further discuss</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: #fafafa; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"><br /></span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: -24px; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: #fafafa;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"><br /></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0in;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: #fafafa; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">Helped Naomi review the GeoComm      project documents. 12-19 and 12-21. Reviewed several of GeoComm project document to ensure consistancy, good quality and overall made sure the documents made sense.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: #fafafa; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">Had a meeting with Mr. Samuels regarding some comments the NOC provided regarding the SLM. 12-19. &nbsp;The NOC provided some comments about the current version of the SLM and he wanted me to contact Gail from the NOC to get clarity with their issues or concerns. &nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: #fafafa; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">Had a meeting with Mr. Samuels and Naomi to discuss the resonse back from the NOC regarding getting more information on their concerns. 12-20. &nbsp;We are setting up a meeting after the holidays to further discuss this matter with the NOC</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>',	'<p>None at this time</p>',	'<p>None at this time</p>',	2,	4,	'2011-12-23 20:14:23',	NULL,	'2011-12-23 22:05:31'),
(10,	3,	2,	1,	'2011-12-30',	'<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Continued to prepare the presentation to the ITIB for requisition of planning funds on 12/27/11.&nbsp; Spoke with Beth via conference call regarding the presentation and provided her with an early draft copy on 12/27/11.&nbsp; She will review with other team members and provide feedback.</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed functional requirements feedback on 12/27/11 and 12/28/11 and communicated concerns to Beth.&nbsp; The concern is that some of the feedback speaks to a solution instead of focusing on functionality.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Mohammad on 12/28/11 to discuss the 200 projects that he is working with in order to understand the relationship to GPI.&nbsp; Form his point of view, the systems that he is involved with will not affect GPI.</p>\r\n<p>Attended WebEx/Conf call on 12/29/11 regarding functional requirements.&nbsp; Beth asked that I speak to the issue of defining requirements and not solutions.&nbsp; The team members on the call were very receptive to this however there still seems to be some confusion in regards to the scope.&nbsp; I stated that WO 500 could not define their scope for them and that they should contact Mike Nedd if they needed scope clarification and he could work with the ITIB to provide answers.</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed and provided comments on 12/30/11 in regards to the meeting notes from the conference call on 12/29/11.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 12/28/11 to discuss the Geospatial Publication Alignment with SLM.&nbsp; We discussed ways of focusing a business on the needs versus the solution.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 12/30/11 to discuss system duplication issues within in BLM and how SLM can help address the issue.&nbsp; We discussed the need to emphasize the importance of Enterprise Architecture before starting any project.</p>\r\n<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Reviewed the New Media Strategy and Presentation on 12/30/11.&nbsp; Waiting on additional feedback from Al\'Tariq and Team Leads.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Provided Beth with an early draft copy of the ITIB presentation on 12/27/11.</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed  functional requirements feedback on 12/27/11 and 12/28/11 and  communicated concerns to Beth.&nbsp; The concern is that some of the feedback  speaks to a solution instead of focusing on functionality.</p>\r\n<p>Met  with Mohammad on 12/28/11 to discuss the 200 projects that he is working  with in order to understand the relationship to GPI.&nbsp; Form his point of  view, the systems that he is involved with will not affect GPI.</p>\r\n<p>Attended  WebEx/Conf call on 12/29/11 regarding functional requirements and provided information on proper project plannign steps.</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed and provided comments on 12/30/11 in regards to the meeting notes from the conference call on 12/29/11.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met  with Fred on 12/28/11 to discuss the Geospatial Publication Alignment  with SLM.&nbsp; We discussed ways of focusing a business on the needs versus  the solution.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 12/30/11 to discuss system  duplication issues within in BLM and how SLM can help address the  issue.&nbsp; We discussed the need to emphasize the importance of Enterprise  Architecture before starting any project.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met  with Mohammad on 12/28/11 to discuss the 200 projects that he is working  with in order to understand the relationship to GPI.&nbsp; Form his point of  view, the systems that he is involved with will not affect GPI.</p>\r\n<p>Attended  WebEx/Conf call on 12/29/11 regarding functional requirements.&nbsp; Beth  asked that I speak to the issue of defining requirements and not  solutions.&nbsp; The team members on the call were very receptive to this  however there still seems to be some confusion in regards to the scope.&nbsp;  I stated that WO 500 could not define their scope for them and that  they should contact Mike Nedd if they needed scope clarification and he  could work with the ITIB to provide answers.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met  with Fred on 12/28/11 to discuss the Geospatial Publication Alignment  with SLM.&nbsp; We discussed ways of focusing a business on the needs versus  the solution.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 12/30/11 to discuss system  duplication issues within in BLM and how SLM can help address the  issue.&nbsp; We discusse the need to emphasize the importance of Enterprise  Architecture before starting any project.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>na</p>',	'<p>na</p>',	2,	4,	'2011-12-30 17:15:48',	NULL,	'2012-01-05 01:32:05'),
(11,	6,	1,	1,	'2011-12-30',	'<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Reviewed additional GeoComm project documents for Naomi that she has recently completed/edited.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Had discussion with Naomi regarding the GeoComm project she is currently working on.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Worked on the SLM Acquisition Strategy template. &nbsp;Make the changes noted by Kim Ashby (IT Acquisitions) in her review of this document.&nbsp; Will need to have her review this document again.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Worked on making the recommended changes to the SLM Business Case template.&nbsp; Added a section for functional requirements.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Worked on the SLM Project Charter template.&nbsp; Made some changes/edits to make the roles and responsibilities easy to understand.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Had several discussions and emails with Mr. Leonard Gore (from BLM GIS group) to discuss their current need for help in the area of GIS.&nbsp; They are looking for some help to get some flex viewer maps online that will benefit the Washington Office.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Worked on getting together some records management templates that we can add to the SLM repository.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in;\">Followed up with Lauren Clapp and the status of the SLM note to reviewer and SLM IM.</span></li>\r\n</ul>',	'<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12pt;\">Completed review the GeoComm document for Naomi and provided my feedback.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt;\">Discussed with Naomi how we can get GeoComm aligned with SLM.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">Discussed with Naomi BLM system duplication issues.</span></li>\r\n</ul>',	'<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Met with Naomi to review additional draft GeoComm project documents. 12-27 and 12-28. Reviewed several of GeoComm project document to ensure consistancy, good quality and overall made sure the documents made sense.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Also met with Naomi to discuss a few of the current issues the GeoComm business project team is having regarding defining boundaries for the scope of the project.&nbsp; 12-28 and 12-29. The business is currently having problems/issues in deciding what to include in the scope of the project.&nbsp; Looking at how we can assist the business by providing clear understanding of what they have to do.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in;\">Met with Mr. Leonard Gore (from BLM GIS group) to discuss their current need for help if the area of GIS.&nbsp; 12-28. &nbsp;They are looking for some help to get some flex viewer maps online that will benefit the Washington Office.&nbsp; We met at his office and he walked me through the manual process of how they currently create maps that they use.&nbsp; They are currently looking for ways to automate this manual process and for an easy way to easily create new maps in the future.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Had several phone conversations with Mr. Leonard Gore to discuss some emails that he wanted me to look at relating to GIS. 12-28 and 12-29.&nbsp; Sent me some emails of potential solutions he was currently looking at.&nbsp; We discussed them and will be further talking next week after the New Year&rsquo;s break is over.&nbsp; Mr. Leonard Gore also mentioned that he will talk to Mr. Samuels to see how we can help him with this effort.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Met with Naomi to discuss how we can get GeoComm aligned with SLM. 12-28</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Met with Naomi to discuss the current problem BLM has with duplicate systems. 12-30</span></li>\r\n</ul>',	'<p><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa;\">None at this time</span></p>',	'<p><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa;\">None at this time</span></p>',	2,	4,	'2011-12-30 17:48:25',	NULL,	'2012-01-05 01:33:18'),
(12,	3,	2,	1,	'2012-01-06',	'<p><strong>Unified Communication</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Mohammad to discuss Unified Communication on 1/3/11.&nbsp; Forwarded him a presentation regarding how to present it to upper management.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth 1/4/11 regarding WO 300\'s presentation to Mike Nedd regarding the status and the scope concerns.&nbsp; Compiled slides for their afternoon presentation.&nbsp; Al\'Tariq requested that we present information regarding the status of GPI to Ms. Levine on 1/4/11 prior to her meeting with Mr. Nedd on 1/5/11.&nbsp; Prepared a status presentation to present to Ms. Levine on 1/4/11.&nbsp; The presentation was approved by Mr. Samuels.&nbsp; Al\'Tariq, Mr. Lewis and myself met with Ms. Levine on 1/4/11 to discuss GPI and AFMSS.&nbsp; Ms. Levine reviewed the information and informed us that the ITIB would likely be postponed.&nbsp; She informed us that user groups needed to be part of our effort and that a lead should be chosen outside of WO300 and WO500.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Mohammad on 1/4/11 to dicuss NISMS and GPI scopes.&nbsp; He was unsure of NISMS scope so we could not define overlap.&nbsp; We disussed the need for a site where everyone could share information about projects they are working on and the status.</p>\r\n<p><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <w:WordDocument> <w:View>Normal</w:View> <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom> <w:TrackMoves /> <w:TrackFormatting /> <w:PunctuationKerning /> <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas /> <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid> <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent> <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText> <w:DoNotPromoteQF /> <w:LidThemeOther>EN-US</w:LidThemeOther> <w:LidThemeAsian>X-NONE</w:LidThemeAsian> <w:LidThemeComplexScript>X-NONE</w:LidThemeComplexScript> <w:Compatibility> <w:BreakWrappedTables /> <w:SnapToGridInCell /> <w:WrapTextWithPunct /> <w:UseAsianBreakRules /> <w:DontGrowAutofit /> <w:SplitPgBreakAn