(21,	3,	2,	1,	'2012-02-03',	'<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Finalized meeting with Neil, Ronnie and Janet along with a meeting with Ronnie and Carole Pfisterer Carter on 1/30/12.&nbsp; The meetings are scheduled for 2/16/12.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq on 1/31/12 to discuss his meeting with Kaveh regarding his stance on the New Media Strategy.&nbsp; Kaveh conveyed that he and WO 600 would not support a New Media Strategy where internal and external efforts were combined.&nbsp; He stated that they had to be two separate strategies and that the external strategy would come from WO 600. I expressed concern that Ronnie is unaware of this as we move forward with the additional meetings.&nbsp; Al\'Tariq stated that he agreed that Ronnie needed to be made aware and that he would share the information with her.&nbsp; He also asked that I review the Strategy again and ensure that WO 600\'s objectives are incorporated.&nbsp; I reviewed the Strategy, ensured incorporation of all objectives and added WO-600\'s \'Strategies\' under Next Steps.&nbsp; This was submitted to Al\'Tariq for review on 2/1/12 for review.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Tablets/Smartphones</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Brian and Al\'Tariq to discuss items needed for the Tablet and Smartphone Inventory on 1/31/12.&nbsp; Created a spreadsheet for tracking of Tablets and Iphones including a section for business need.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Discussed the need for a clear written scope with Beth on 2/1/12.&nbsp; Provided her with a request for a meeting on 2/3/12.&nbsp; We will be meeting on Tuesday 2/7/12.&nbsp; Provided her with notification that the ITIB will meet on 3/1/12.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Quicktime IM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Prepared an IM for the release of an application for remote access to Quicktime per Al\'Tariq\'s request on 2/2/12.&nbsp; Submitted it to Al\'Tariq on 2/2/12 and followed up with a meeting to discuss the language.&nbsp; He approved the IM but we did not have access to the needed attachments for the IM.&nbsp; Coordinated with DOI to get the needed attachments for the IM.&nbsp; Worked with Lauren on 2/3/12 to package the IM. This included preparation of a Note to Reviewer.&nbsp; Prepared an email on 2/3/12 announcing the release of the application and submitted it to Al\'Tariq for review.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 2/1/12 and 2/2/12 to discuss CPIC\'s comments regarding the SLM.&nbsp; Reviewed responses and provided responses to Fred that were specific to Project Management Insitute\'s (PMI\'s) Project Management Body of Knowledge (PMBOK)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Finalized meeting with Neil, Ronnie  and Janet along with a meeting with Ronnie and Carole Pfisterer Carter  on 1/30/12.&nbsp; The meetings are scheduled for 2/16/12.</p>\r\n<p>Met with  Al\'Tariq on 1/31/12 to discuss his meeting with Kaveh regarding his  stance on the New Media Strategy. He asked that I review the Strategy again and ensure that WO  600\'s objectives are incorporated.&nbsp; Reviewed the Strategy, ensured  incorporation of all objectives and added WO-600\'s \'Strategies\' under  Next Steps.&nbsp; This was submitted to Al\'Tariq for review on 2/1/12 for  review.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Tablets/Smartphones</strong></p>\r\n<p>Created a spreadsheet for tracking of Tablets  and Iphones including a section for business need.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Discussed  the need for a clear written scope with Beth on 2/1/12.&nbsp; Provided her  with a request for a meeting on 2/3/12.&nbsp; We will be meeting on Tuesday  2/7/12.&nbsp; Provided her with notification that the ITIB will meet on  3/1/12.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Quicktime IM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Prepared an IM for the  release of an application for remote access to Quicktime per Al\'Tariq\'s  request on 2/2/12.&nbsp; Submitted it to Al\'Tariq on 2/2/12 and followed up  with a meeting to discuss the language.&nbsp; He approved the IM but we did  not have access to the needed attachments for the IM.&nbsp; Coordinated with  DOI to get the needed attachments for the IM.&nbsp; Worked with Lauren on  2/3/12 to package the IM. This included preparation of a Note to  Reviewer.&nbsp; Prepared an email on 2/3/12 announcing the release of the  application and submitted it to Al\'Tariq for review.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 2/1/12 and 2/2/12  to discuss CPIC\'s comments regarding the SLM.&nbsp; Reviewed responses and  provided responses to Fred that were specific to Project Management  Insitute\'s (PMI\'s) Project Management Body of Knowledge (PMBOK).</p>',	'<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with  Al\'Tariq on 1/31/12 to discuss his meeting with Kaveh regarding his  stance on the New Media Strategy.&nbsp; Kaveh conveyed that he and WO 600  would not support a New Media Strategy where internal and external  efforts were combined.&nbsp; He stated that they had to be two separate  strategies and that the external strategy would come from WO 600. I  expressed concern that Ronnie is unaware of this as we move forward with  the additional meetings.&nbsp; Al\'Tariq stated that he agreed that Ronnie  needed to be made aware and that he would share the information with  her.&nbsp; He also asked that I review the Strategy again and ensure that WO  600\'s objectives are incorporated.&nbsp; I reviewed the Strategy, ensured  incorporation of all objectives and added WO-600\'s \'Strategies\' under  Next Steps.&nbsp; This was submitted to Al\'Tariq for review on 2/1/12 for  review.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Tablets/Smartphones</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with  Brian and Al\'Tariq to discuss items needed for the Tablet and Smartphone  Inventory on 1/31/12.&nbsp; Created a spreadsheet for tracking of Tablets  and Iphones including a section for business need.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Quicktime IM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq on 2/2/12 to discuss the language in the Quicktime IM.&nbsp; He approved the IM but we did  not have access to the needed attachments for the IM.&nbsp; Coordinated with  DOI to get the needed attachments for the IM.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 2/1/12 and 2/2/12  to discuss CPIC\'s comments regarding the SLM.&nbsp; Reviewed responses and  provided responses to Fred that were specific to Project Management  Insitute\'s (PMI\'s) Project Management Body of Knowledge (PMBOK)</p>',	'<p>na</p>',	'<p>na</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-02-03 21:46:45',	NULL,	'2012-02-11 00:34:14'),
(22,	6,	1,	1,	'2012-02-10',	'<ul>\r\n<li>Worked on the remaining sections of the SLM presentation. &nbsp;Will submit the presentation to Mr. Samuels as soon as I finish for his review.</li>\r\n<li>Review the&nbsp;Walk the Walk Support Team project plan in preparation for our team meeting.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Started cleaning up my area.</li>\r\n<li>Started organizing files that I have been working on so I can put them on the BLM share drive.</li>\r\n<li>Getting together all BLM file that I have been working on so I can put them on the BLM network (S: drive)</li>\r\n<li>Sent Mr. Lewis and Mr. Springfield emails of the location of where I put all the files I have been working on.</li>\r\n</ul>',	'<ul>\r\n<li>Completed the SLM presentation and emailed it to Mr. Samuels. &nbsp;The presentation contained the remainder of the SLM phases (Requirements Analysis through Disposition) that will need to be presented to Ms. Levine for her approval.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Put all BLM file that I have been working on onto the shared drive on the BLM network (S: drive)</li>\r\n<li>Sent Mr. Lewis and Mr. Springfield emails of the location of where I put all the files I have been working on.</li>\r\n<li>Almost finished cleaning up my work area.</li>\r\n</ul>',	'<ul>\r\n<li>2-7-12: Had a meeting with our Walk the Walk Support Team to review and discuss the project plan for the project and our group. &nbsp;The project plan did not have sufficient information for us to complete the task of creating a project timeline. &nbsp;Team lead will look to get the information we need to complet assignment. &nbsp;The team lead will be setting up a demo of the Data Tracking System (DTS) that we discussing during our meeting.</li>\r\n<li>2-8-12: Had a meeting with Mr. Lewis and Mr. Springfield regarding the status of my current contract with Atechra in support of BLM.</li>\r\n</ul>',	'<p>None at this time.</p>',	'<p>None at this time.</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-02-09 17:53:21',	6,	'2012-02-14 17:40:23'),
(23,	3,	2,	1,	'2012-02-10',	'<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Provided Al\'Tariq and Ronnie with information from DOI regarding New Media and Twitter on 2/6/12.<strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Ronnie, Bob Abbey, Kevah, Celia, Craig, Neil and several other BLM staff to review Social Media presentations from California, Colorado and Oregon on 2/7/12.&nbsp; Ronnie requested that I provide the latest New Media presentation so that she could present our work eventhough the Core Team of Executives had not reviewed this.&nbsp; I notified her that WO 600 may not agree with all of the Next Steps per previous conversations.&nbsp; Kaveh presented a External New Media Strategy at the meeting which was closely related to the strategy that his team presented in regards to the overall strategy.&nbsp; He had not shared that he would be presenting this.&nbsp; Neil and Mr. Abbey both liked the states presentations, especially Oregon.&nbsp; They are interested in seeing the Washington Office provide an effort that integrates both internal and external items. .</p>\r\n<p>Provided updated New Media Strategy and Presentation to Al\'Tariq on 2/8/12.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Offsite With Ronnie</strong></p>\r\n<p>Attended off-site meeting in Falls Church Va with Ronnie Levine, Lara Douglas and Ore Fashola at Noblis on 2/7/12.&nbsp; We discussed solutions that they had provided to other government entities.&nbsp; The took us through several technology simulations.&nbsp; Ronnie and I discussed how projects such as GPI and AFMSS could benefit from outside technical consulting due to their complexity and the availability of new technology.&nbsp; If we limit solutions to just what we know, we limit the projects.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Discussed the need for the updated Charter and Scope Statement for GPI with Beth on 2/6/12.&nbsp; We scheduled a meeting for 2/8/12.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Beth and Dan on 2/8/12 to discuss the status of GPI and what exactly was needed for the ITIB.&nbsp; We compiled a list of the following questions and submitted them to Al\'Tariq: WO 300 will need and inventory of existing geospatial display applications used across BLM.&nbsp; Who can request that states and other offices submit existing and planned applications and who will handle the registration of these?&nbsp; It is part of the EA function so will WO 500 manage this?&nbsp;&nbsp;The development of new other geospatial display applications is a major concern for this investment because this is a bureau wide effort.&nbsp; If development of separate applications continues, the benefit of having a bureau wide solution is diminished because businesses will have created their own smaller scale solutions that meet their needs without meeting the bureau&rsquo;s need to have a single resource to view the data.&nbsp; However, there is a need for certain application developments in order for businesses to carry on their everyday business.&nbsp; Will WO 300, WO 500 or the ITIB decide which applications are allowed to continue development?&nbsp; Will WO 500 issue policy regarding this because issuing policy is considered a WO 500 function?&nbsp;&nbsp;Geocommunicator&rsquo;s existing support contract expires in March.&nbsp; WO 300 has been paying this contract but it supports data that is not owned by WO 300.&nbsp; Is WO 300 obligated to continue to support this contract?&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <o:OfficeDocumentSettings> <o:AllowPNG /> </o:OfficeDocumentSettings> </xml><![endif][if gte mso 9]><xml> <w:WordDocument> <w:View>Normal</w:View> <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom> <w:TrackMoves /> <w:TrackFormatting /> <w:PunctuationKerning /> <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas /> <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid> <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent> <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText> <w:DoNotPromoteQF /> <w:LidThemeOther>EN-US</w:LidThemeOther> <w:LidThemeAsian>X-NO