le-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-priority:99;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin-top:0in;\r\n	mso-para-margin-right:0in;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:10.0pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin-left:0in;\r\n	line-height:115%;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:11.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Calibri\",\"sans-serif\";\r\n	mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;\r\n	mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\n	mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;\r\n	mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\n	mso-bidi-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Al\'Tariq on 2/8/12 to discuss the questions above an he provided the following answers: WO 500 will develop a request for applications information (in the form of an IM) and provide WO 300 with information regarding geospatial data display applications. The ITIB will likely need to make the final decision.<span>&nbsp; </span>WO 300 and WO 500 should work together to provide recommendations once the inventory has been completed and reviewed.<span>&nbsp; </span>WO 300&rsquo;s AD will need to address the support contract and work with the ITIB if necessary to come to a decision.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Submitted basic draft presentation for ITIB to Beth on 2/9/12.<span>&nbsp; </span>She will review and provide updates from the business.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Coordinated with WO 300 and WO 550 to try to establish baseline costs for planning.<span>&nbsp; </span>Received feedback from Sayed that the cost of planning for NILS was $2million.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Worked with Beth to updated and review the Charter on 2/9/12 and 2/10/12.<span>&nbsp; </span>Updated the Risk Management Plan, Acquisition Management Plan, Change Management Plan, Quality Management Plan, Work Breakdown Structure, Staffing Plan, Project Management Plan and Business Case Document to reflect the changes in the scope on 2/9/12 and 2/10/12.<span>&nbsp; </span>These documents are only partially completed and will be completed during the Planning Phase.<span>&nbsp; </span>Requested Beth submit the Scope Statement prior to the meeting on Monday morning.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred to discuss the status of GPI and how it was aligning with SLM on 2/6/12.&nbsp; We discussed the need for the role of SLM to be clarified between all divisions on WO500.<strong><br /></strong></p>',	'<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Provided Al\'Tariq and Ronnie with information from DOI regarding New Media and Twitter on 2/6/12.<strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p>Met  with Ronnie, Bob Abbey, Kevah, Celia, Craig, Neil and several other BLM  staff to review Social Media presentations from California, Colorado  and Oregon on 2/7/12.</p>\r\n<p>Provided updated New Media Strategy and Presentation to Al\'Tariq on 2/8/12.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Offsite With Ronnie</strong></p>\r\n<p>Attended off-site meeting  in Falls Church Va with Ronnie Levine, Lara Douglas and Ore Fashola at  Noblis on 2/7/12.&nbsp;&nbsp; Ronnie and I discussed how projects such as GPI and AFMSS  could benefit from outside technical consulting due to their complexity  and the availability of new technology.&nbsp; If we limit solutions to just  what we know, we limit the projects.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Discussed the need for the updated Charter and Scope Statement for GPI with Beth on 2/6/12.&nbsp; We scheduled a meeting for 2/8/12.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Beth and Dan on 2/8/12 to discuss the status of GPI and what exactly was needed for the ITIB.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Al\'Tariq on 2/8/12 to discuss the questions in regards to the GPI meeting.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Submitted basic draft presentation for ITIB to Beth on 2/9/12.<span>&nbsp; </span>She will review and provide updates from the business.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Coordinated with WO 300 and WO 550 to try to establish baseline costs for planning.<span>&nbsp; </span>Received feedback from Sayed that the cost of planning for NILS was $2million.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Worked with Beth to updated and review the Charter on 2/9/12 and 2/10/12.<span>&nbsp; </span>Updated the Risk Management Plan, Acquisition Management Plan, Change Management Plan, Quality Management Plan, Work Breakdown Structure, Staffing Plan, Project Management Plan and Business Case Document to reflect the changes in the scope on 2/9/12 and 2/10/12.<span>&nbsp; </span>These documents are only partially completed and will be completed during the Planning Phase.<span>&nbsp; </span>Requested Beth submit the Scope Statement prior to the meeting on Monday morning.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred to discuss the status of GPI  and how it was aligning with SLM on 2/6/12.&nbsp; We discussed the need for  the role of SLM to be clarified between all divisions on WO500.<strong><br /></strong></p>',	'<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met  with Ronnie, Bob Abbey, Kevah, Celia, Craig, Neil and several other BLM  staff to review Social Media presentations from California, Colorado  and Oregon on 2/7/12.&nbsp; Ronnie requested that I provide the latest New  Media presentation so that she could present our work eventhough the  Core Team of Executives had not reviewed this.&nbsp; I notified her that WO  600 may not agree with all of the Next Steps per previous  conversations.&nbsp; Kaveh presented a External New Media Strategy at the  meeting which was closely related to the strategy that his team  presented in regards to the overall strategy.&nbsp; He had not shared that he  would be presenting this.&nbsp; Neil and Mr. Abbey both liked the states  presentations, especially Oregon.&nbsp; They are interested in seeing the  Washington Office provide an effort that integrates both internal and  external items. .</p>\r\n<p><strong>Offsite With Ronnie</strong></p>\r\n<p>Attended off-site meeting  in Falls Church Va with Ronnie Levine, Lara Douglas and Ore Fashola at  Noblis on 2/7/12.&nbsp; We discussed solutions that they had provided to  other government entities.&nbsp; The took us through several technology  simulations.&nbsp; Ronnie and I discussed how projects such as GPI and AFMSS  could benefit from outside technical consulting due to their complexity  and the availability of new technology.&nbsp; If we limit solutions to just  what we know, we limit the projects.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Beth and Dan on 2/8/12 to discuss the status of GPI and what exactly was needed for the ITIB.&nbsp;  We compiled a list of the following questions and submitted them to  Al\'Tariq: WO 300 will need and inventory of existing geospatial display applications used across BLM.&nbsp; Who can request that states and other offices submit existing and planned applications and who will  handle the registration of these?&nbsp; It is part of the EA function so will WO 500 manage this?&nbsp;&nbsp;The development of new other geospatial display applications is a major concern for this investment because this is a bureau wide effort.&nbsp; If development of separate applications continues, the benefit of having a bureau wide solution is diminished because businesses will have created their own smaller scale solutions that meet their needs without meeting the bureau&rsquo;s need to have a single resource to view the data.&nbsp; However, there is a need for certain application developments in order for businesses to carry on their everyday business.&nbsp; Will WO 300, WO 500 or the ITIB decide which applications are allowed to continue development?&nbsp; Will WO 500 issue policy regarding this because issuing policy is considered a WO 500 function?&nbsp;&nbsp;Geocommunicator&rsquo;s existing support contract expires in March.&nbsp; WO 300 has been paying this contract but it supports data that is not owned by WO 300.&nbsp; Is WO 300 obligated to continue to support this contract?&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Al\'Tariq on 2/8/12 to discuss the questions above an he provided the following answers: WO 500 will develop a request for applications information (in the form of an IM) and provide WO 300 with information regarding geospatial data display applications. The ITIB will likely need to make the final decision.<span>&nbsp; </span>WO 300 and WO 500 should work together to provide recommendations once the inventory has been completed and reviewed.<span>&nbsp; </span>WO 300&rsquo;s AD will need to address the support contract and work with the ITIB if necessary to come to a decision.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred to discuss the status of GPI  and how it was aligning with SLM on 2/6/12.&nbsp; We discussed the need for  the role of SLM to be clarified between all divisions on WO500.<strong><br /></strong></p>',	'<p>na</p>',	'<p>na</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-02-11 00:05:53',	3,	'2012-02-14 17:43:25'),
(24,	6,	1,	1,	'2012-02-17',	'<ul style=\"background-color: #fafafa; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; margin: 0px;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Review the&nbsp;Walk the Walk Support Team revised project plan.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Cleaned up my area.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Put all BLM file that I have been working on so I can put them on the BLM network (S: drive)</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Created backup cd\'s with BLM data to turn over to Atechra.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<div>\r\n<ul style=\"padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Put additional BLM file that I have been working on onto the shared drive on the BLM network (S: drive)</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Finished cleaning up my work area.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Gave Atechra 3 cd\'s with all the BLM data that I have been working on. &nbsp;The cd\'s contain all the completed SLM documents (Technical Manual, User Manual and all the required artifacts/templates that is required for the SLM process. &nbsp;The cd\'s also contains all the presentations, suggestions and other documents/projects items that I have worked during my time at BLM.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Gave Atechra all BLM property including any badge or key that I had.</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Completely checked out of BLM and removed all my personal property.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<ul style=\"padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; background-color: #fafafa; margin: 0px;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\">2-14-12: Had a demo of the Data Tracking System (DTS). &nbsp;This was not a live demo due to some login issues. &nbsp;The DTS person walked us through some screenshots in the user manual.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>None at this time.</p>',	'<p>None at this time.</p>',	2,	2,	'2012-02-14 23:05:53',	6,	'2012-04-02 20:54:08'),
(25,	3,	2,	1,	'2012-02-17',	'<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Attended webiner on 2/15/12 regarding the legal issues of social media. The potential legal issues that can arise from social networking activities are extensive. Privacy, unauthorized activities, and intellectual property issues stand top-of-mind for many individuals and enterprises. Other areas, such as content ownership, regulatory compliance, and even criminal activity, are impacted by social media, too.&nbsp; This webinar provided information in regards to these issues.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Kaveh on 2/15/12 to discuss Social Media, our Intranet and the Oregon solution. Oregon is currently using Sharepoint for their Intranet and they post to it when they post to the external social media sites.&nbsp; Our current Intranet uses php.&nbsp; Kaveh stated that there was an IM issued that prevents development in Sharepoint.&nbsp; He also stated that the NOC released a million dollar contract to develop in Sharepoint 2010 but didn&rsquo;t know what it was in regards to.&nbsp; He said that DOI has a Sharepoint 2010 farm that we might could leverage and that WO 600 would use Sharepoint or another technology if we suggested it. I provided this information to Al\'Tariq on 2/15/12.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Al\'Tariq on 2/16/12 to discuss the meeting with Kaveh.&nbsp; We called Lloyd in Oregon who said we should contact Aaron Haselby.&nbsp; I left a message with Aaron on 2/16/12.&nbsp; Al\'Tariq wants to know how complicated it would be for us to duplicate what Oregon is doing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth and Dan on 2/13/12 to discuss the Investment and the status of ITIB items.&nbsp; They are on track but need to revise the cahrter again because it includes a few items that are too technical.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth, Dan, Don, Kim and Al\'Tariq on 2/13/12 to discuss ITIB presentation.&nbsp; Kim requested that scope slides be added.&nbsp; Al\'Tariq stated that they should address the GeoCommunicator support contract issue, provide costs for planning and how they were attained along with a timeline and interim plans.&nbsp; Beth will update the presentation for review this week.</p>\r\n<p>Researched planning costs and referenced GSA contracts.&nbsp; Provided costs to Beth for reference on 2/13/12.</p>\r\n<p>Updated Work Breakdown Structure and graphic on 2/13/12.&nbsp; Provide this to Beth.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed updated planning documents on 2/14/12.&nbsp; Provided an Executive Summary to Al\'Tariq for review and then provided the approved Summary to Beth on 2/14/12.&nbsp; Updated draft documents with a watermark and provided them to Beth.&nbsp; Reformatted the Charter for consistency and provided Beth with the document.</p>\r\n<p>Provided Beth with reformatted Scope Statement on 2/17/12.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth on 2/17/12 to review and request a copy of the updated presentation.&nbsp; She provided this and I forward it to Al\'Tariq.&nbsp; She also stated that they had planned meetings with the ITIB members on an individual basis but had not notified WO500 of this but had invited Ronnie who is out.&nbsp; Provided this information to Al\'Tariq.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq to discuss the meeting with Beth on 2/17/12.&nbsp; He asked that I provide them feedback noting that we were concerned because Ronnie had not seen the materials and because the ITIB members may not understand why they needed to meet twice about it. Sent her an email with the notes.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Field Focused Team</strong></p>\r\n<p>Attended Document Tracking System Demonstration on 2/15/12.&nbsp; Discussed the benefits of this system with WO 500.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Systems/Applications Inventory</strong></p>\r\n<p>Reviewed Inventory Documents that Al\'Tariq provided on 2/16/12.&nbsp; The spreadsheet remains incomplete and the biggest concern is that there isnt a description for the functionality of systems/applications. Provided Al\'Tariq with feedback on 2/16/12.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Staff Meeting</strong></p>\r\n<p>Attended staff meeting on 2/15/12.&nbsp; Team discussed goals of WO500, WO570 and BLM overall.&nbsp; We were requested to provide our short term and long term goals to Al\'Tariq and Ken.&nbsp; Provided a list of goals via email on 2/15/12.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Reviewed information provided by Security on 2/16/12.&nbsp; They have specified information that they would like incorporated during different phases of project development.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Attended webiner on 2/15/12  regarding the legal issues of social media.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Kaveh on 2/15/12 to discuss Social Media,  our Intranet and the Oregon solution.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Al\'Tariq on 2/16/12 to discuss the meeting  with Kaveh.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with  Beth and Dan on 2/13/12 to discuss the Investment and the status of ITIB  items.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth,  Dan, Don, Kim and Al\'Tariq on 2/13/12 to discuss ITIB presentation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Researched planning costs and referenced GSA contracts.&nbsp; Provided costs to Beth for reference on 2/13/12.</p>\r\n<p>Updated Work Breakdown Structure and graphic on 2/13/12.&nbsp; Provide this to Beth.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed  updated planning documents on 2/14/12.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Provided an Executive Summary  to Al\'Tariq for review and then provided the approved Summary to Beth on  2/14/12.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Updated draft documents with a watermark and provided them to  Beth.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Reformatted the Charter for consistency and provided Beth with  the document.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth on 2/17/12 to review and request a copy of the updated  presentation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Provided Beth with reformatted Scope Statement on 2/17/12.</p>\r\n<p>Met  with Al\'Tariq to discuss th