wtext .5pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid windowtext .5pt;\" width=\"152\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Kerry</span></span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 15pt; mso-yfti-irow: 20;\">\r\n<td style=\"border-bottom: windowtext 1pt solid; border-left: windowtext 1pt solid; padding-bottom: 0in; background-color: transparent; padding-left: 5.4pt; width: 443pt; padding-right: 5.4pt; height: 15pt; border-top: #f0f0f0; border-right: windowtext 1pt solid; padding-top: 0in; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid windowtext .5pt;\" width=\"591\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">The Big Idea</span></span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border-bottom: windowtext 1pt solid; border-left: #f0f0f0; padding-bottom: 0in; background-color: transparent; padding-left: 5.4pt; width: 114pt; padding-right: 5.4pt; height: 15pt; border-top: #f0f0f0; border-right: windowtext 1pt solid; padding-top: 0in; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid windowtext .5pt;\" width=\"152\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Mohammad</span></span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 15pt; mso-yfti-irow: 21;\">\r\n<td style=\"border-bottom: windowtext 1pt solid; border-left: windowtext 1pt solid; padding-bottom: 0in; background-color: transparent; padding-left: 5.4pt; width: 443pt; padding-right: 5.4pt; height: 15pt; border-top: #f0f0f0; border-right: windowtext 1pt solid; padding-top: 0in; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid windowtext .5pt;\" width=\"591\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Wireless Access on BLM Laptops</span></span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border-bottom: windowtext 1pt solid; border-left: #f0f0f0; padding-bottom: 0in; background-color: transparent; padding-left: 5.4pt; width: 114pt; padding-right: 5.4pt; height: 15pt; border-top: #f0f0f0; border-right: windowtext 1pt solid; padding-top: 0in; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid windowtext .5pt;\" width=\"152\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Mohammad</span></span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 15pt; mso-yfti-irow: 22;\">\r\n<td style=\"border-bottom: windowtext 1pt solid; border-left: windowtext 1pt solid; padding-bottom: 0in; background-color: transparent; padding-left: 5.4pt; width: 443pt; padding-right: 5.4pt; height: 15pt; border-top: #f0f0f0; border-right: windowtext 1pt solid; padding-top: 0in; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid windowtext .5pt;\" width=\"591\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Workstation (Desktops and Laptops) Ration Reduction Plan</span></span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border-bottom: windowtext 1pt solid; border-left: #f0f0f0; padding-bottom: 0in; background-color: transparent; padding-left: 5.4pt; width: 114pt; padding-right: 5.4pt; height: 15pt; border-top: #f0f0f0; border-right: windowtext 1pt solid; padding-top: 0in; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid windowtext .5pt;\" width=\"152\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Patrick</span></span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 15pt; mso-yfti-irow: 23; mso-yfti-lastrow: yes;\">\r\n<td style=\"border-bottom: windowtext 1pt solid; border-left: windowtext 1pt solid; padding-bottom: 0in; background-color: transparent; padding-left: 5.4pt; width: 443pt; padding-right: 5.4pt; height: 15pt; border-top: #f0f0f0; border-right: windowtext 1pt solid; padding-top: 0in; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid windowtext .5pt;\" width=\"591\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Enterprise Architecture Support</span></span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border-bottom: windowtext 1pt solid; border-left: #f0f0f0; padding-bottom: 0in; background-color: transparent; padding-left: 5.4pt; width: 114pt; padding-right: 5.4pt; height: 15pt; border-top: #f0f0f0; border-right: windowtext 1pt solid; padding-top: 0in; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid windowtext .5pt;\" width=\"152\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Paul</span></span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">SLM</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">I reviewed and prepared extensive written comments and a revised flowchart on the System Lifecycle Management document.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>The flowchart explains each phase and also the relationship of the Business Technology and Alignment division to the Information Technology Investment Board (ITIB).<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>While the clear intent of the document is to provide an integrated lifecycle framework for BLM, there are elements within the document that have retain a system level perspective.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>In addition to having spoken with several critical partners about my perspective of the SLM, each has distinctly different observations about the readiness of the SLM in its current state which may not adequately speak to enterprise level risks within an integrated life cycle framework.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>To date, feedback on the SLM has been provided by the following; Capital Planning and Investment Control (CPIC), Enterprise Architecture and IT Security.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Al&rsquo; Tariq expressed intent to facilitate a broader level of discussions with many of the Critical Partners who are continuing to review the SLM during the week of March 26<sup>th</sup>.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>I anticipate this discussion to be enlarged upon the discussions that I have previously had with Mr. J.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>McMahon, IT Transformation Coordinator, Mr. Eichenbaum of IT Security and Mr. P. Stingley, Chief Technology Officer. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\">Data Consolidation Plan</span></strong>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Al&rsquo; Tariq Samuels introduced Patrick Stingley, BLM Chief Technology Officer, who along with Ronnie Levine, BLM Chief Information Officer are jointly responsible for the Data Center Consolidation program.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span>WO-570 will assist with governance whereas the Network Operations Center will handle all physical layers of the data center consolidation.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span>Patrick Stingley discussed with me the need to consolidate 51 data centers into 4. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>While there are (were) 5 data centers that have been running GIS, this number will need to be brought down to 3.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span>Most data centers have only three servers (e.g. file server, print server and data server).<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span>GIS is on RAID 5 and should be on RAID 1.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span>WO-570 does not yet know precisely how the consolidation ideally should be staggered but the consolidation has to be done based upon our assessment of (i) nature of technology resources used and also (ii) physical equipment at each data center.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span>To accomplish this task, an application development assessment tool is being used to assess the data centers for all applications that are on servers in BLM.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span>WO-570 wants to know what information is needed and how we want that information.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span>One of the biggest challenges is that since there have never been any requirements documents standards in BLM, WO-570 needs to build a requirements document with use cases using the Unified Modeling Language and refer to Rational Unified Process.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span>As the assigned project manager, I will maintain a project schedule using MS Project or Excel in a Gant format, and lead efforts to build a complete requirements document.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span>Fundamental knowledge principles include understanding RAID 1 through RAID 5 (e.g. the main difference being speed and also redundancy), the differences between a virtual server versus a hard server, and enterprise architecture planning.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">I have requested and received the Data Center Consolidation project plan from Patrick Stingley.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000;\">\r\n<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 12pt;\">Enterprise Architecture</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Patrick Stingley, BLM Chief Technology Officer and I had a discussion on Tuesday, March 20<sup>th</sup> to capture a brief knowledge&nbsp;of experience and background with Enterprise Architecture development.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span>Based on our discussion of BLM\'s need for support in this area, I began a review of several interrelated Enterprise Architecture models (i.e.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span>Performance Reference, Business Reference, Service Component, Data and Information Reference, and Technical Reference) related to BLM.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span></span></p>\r\n</p>\r\n</span></p>\r\n</span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">SLM</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">I reviewed and prepared extensive written comments and a revised flowchart on the System Lifecycle Management document.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;Afterward, </span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">I discussed with&nbsp;Al\'Tariq the need to have a meeting with the Critical Partners.&nbsp; Al\'Tariq has indicated that he will set up this meeting next week.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 12pt;\">Enterprise Architecture</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">To support updates that are needed to the BLM Enterprise Architecture, I provided Patrick with a detailed list of the Unix and Windows platforms used within BLM, as well as a detailed list of all the software applications and databases used in the NOC and field offices.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>This list is also going to be used within the overall scope of the data consolidation plan.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</span>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</span>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\">&nbsp;</p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Meetings and Presentations</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">On Monday, March 21<sup>st</sup> I attended a 3pm (EST) teleconference to learn about the data center consolidation project plan, and the quarterly deliverables in 2012.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Specific questions that were addressed pertain to (a) </span><span style=\"color: black; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Eastern States responsibility as it relates to this project, (b) project manager from the NOC and WO-570, (c) POC\'s at the Cloud project and the feasibility of a meeting with them to discuss the project, (d) who had responsibility to pay for the storage in the cloud, (e) the expectations for implementation of the pilot as it relates to the competitive process and the audience who are observing, (f) the next steps in moving forward</span><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">.</span></span></span></span></p>',	'<p><strong>NA</strong></p>',	'<p><strong>NA</strong></p>',	2,	4,	'2012-03-25 06:51:58',	4,	'2012-03-30 19:37:14'),
(31,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-03-30',	'<p>Continued work on Data Center Consolidation Initiative quarterly report, receiving network input from NOC\'s Doug Sipes and inputting it into the three closure reports.&nbsp; Mr. Stingley requested server data from a source at NOC and was given three semi-completed reports that were filled with errors.&nbsp; Compared&nbsp; those submissions to the data we believed to be correct, highlighted the materials, Mr. Samuels sent the comparisons to Don Ravenscroft @NOC for review.</p>\r\n<p>Continued editing/rewriting the SLM Tech Manual.</p>',	'<p>Polished the three DCCI closure reports to near finished state, pointed out errors, handed off to NOC for final version completion.</p>\r\n<p>Did an edit of the CM Manual and submitted to Naomi Bowers; will do an edit of the Handbook next week.</p>',	'<p>Attended phone meeting with Mr. Samuels, Mr. Stingley and Mr. Ravenscroft, where it was decided that Alex of NOC would be PM, and be responsible for completing documents.</p>\r\n<p>Spent three hours attending phone meeting with Mr. Stingley, Oregon CIO, Alex and Stephanie of NOC.&nbsp; Pat lead them step by step through the documents; I supported Pat (silently)&nbsp;in moving the process forward.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Mr. McAllister to&nbsp;hold initial review of SLM adjustments so far. We are in general agreement on direction,&nbsp;lacks in early part of document.&nbsp; We agreed to submit a name change&nbsp;as ILM--Integrated Lifecycle Management Framework.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Met with Joe McMahon of CPIC&nbsp;to discuss his interests/attitudes about moving SLM forward.&nbsp; He has strong feelings about the approach that must be taken, among other things that it needs to be referred to as the \"Integrated\" Lifecycle Management Framework (I had already changed the document-see above comment).&nbsp; His approach makes sense, but the&nbsp;methodology he portrays is no small&nbsp;task.</p>',	'<p>It is likely that there will continue to be problems with the DCCI closure reports if assignments stay as they are.&nbsp; The situation may resolve itself, since Mr. Ravenscroft attended the coordination session with Mr. Stingley, and saw&nbsp;firsthand the difficulties his people were having.</p>',	'<p>COTR is well aware of the DCCI problems.&nbsp; No further action necessary.</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-03-30 16:26:07',	4,	'2012-04-04 08:25:50'),
(32,	12,	2,	1,	'2012-03-30',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Enterprise Architecture</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">I began an intensive review of the Federal Enterprise Architecture (FEA) standard.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Among the main documents that I have been requested to review are the <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">FEA Consolidated Reference Model Document Version 2.3</span><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"> </span>published by the Office of Management and Budget.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>During the week of April 9<sup>th</sup>, I will discuss the content of standard with the Chief Technology Officer and coordinate additional activities for the Enterprise Architecture development which includes defining the current state and future state.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; One aspect of curent state that </span>I am working&nbsp;requires the manual process of transferring application and server information from a National application server inventory list maintained by the Network Operations Center (NOC) into the Business Reference Model spreadsheet of the FEA. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>The list captures all versions of software applications maintained on both Windows and UNIX server systems. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">Mission Needs Statement (MNS)</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\">I was asked by Patrick Stingley to begin working on a Mission Needs Statement to develop a high performance or optimized Geospatial Information System (GIS).<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Part of this task involves research into render farm companies, and evaluation of particular features of render farms that will be appropriate for BLM systems.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>The goal is that WO-570 develop a high level architecture that will be successfully implemented by BLM personnel at the Network Operations Center.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>The BLM MNS includes the following; i<span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">mpact on BLM mission areas, needed capability, current and planned capability, impact of not approving mission need benefits, timeframe, criticality, and long-range resource planning estimate.</span><strong><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\"> </span></strong></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</span></span></span>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</span>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\">&nbsp;</p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Configuration Management Plan</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Per the request of Al&rsquo;Tariq, all team members were asked to reply with editorial comments to the BLM<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span>Configuration Management Plan.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span>Team members were instructed to provide feedback to Naomi Bowers who would consolidate comments.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span>On Thursday, March 30<sup>th</sup> I&nbsp;completed a review of the&nbsp;Configuration Management Plan and sent&nbsp;revisions to Naomi. I offered to provide clarity or additional information to assist her in compiling her draft due to Al&rsquo;Tariq in early April. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></strong>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">SLM</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">On Monday, March 23, 2012, I participated in a 1.5 hour structured walkthrough of the SLM with James Mattix. Comments and suggested revisions were discussed based on observations and discussions with BLM staff. Approximately two sections of the current version of the SLM were reviewed.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>I provided additional feedback in writing on SLM related areas after the meeting.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</span></span></p>\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">On Monday, March 26, 2012, Al&rsquo;Tariq held a meeting to review project assignments that were documented the previous week.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>During the meeting, main Information Technology categories that have to be addressed for all federal agencies were discussed.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Al&rsquo;Tariq also distributed a Memorandum of Understanding between the National Operations Center (OC-300) and Business and Technology Alignment (WO-570) on BLM Data Center Consolidation.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I was asked to lead Enterprise Architecture projects related to Data Standardization, Inventory and Establishing Guidelines for Legacy Systems, and the Electronic Geospatial Information Systems.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>The Data Center Consolidation project was subsequently reassigned to James Mattix.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">On Monday, March 26<sup>th</sup> Al&rsquo; Tariq Samuels held a division meeting to outline projects and discuss impact of those projects on the overall mission of WTO-570.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Al&rsquo;Tariq announced the pending resignation of Ms. Ronnie Levine as BLM Assistant Director (WO-500). I will follow up on comments that relate to Enterprise Architecture including need for BLM to develop its own Technical Reference Model (TRM).<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Patrick Stingley and I had also briefly discussed this issue.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>It seems that the TRM model under the Federal Enterprise Architecture model does not sufficiently address BLM business needs. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>I was asked to interface with Naomi on IT Portfolio matters, Christine on data standardization and follow-up with Mohammad on efforts involving an IBM Framework.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>During the meeting, Al\'Tariq also requested suggestions for software tools that BLM might use for Portfolio and Project Management and Enterprise Architecture.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I made a recommendation after the meeting for a mature PPM tool (CA Clarity) that Al&rsquo;Tariq stated BLM is already evaluating.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>Each attendee gave a brief summary of their work assignments.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Afterwards the 1 hour meeting was concluded.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt; tab-stops: 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">na</span></span></span></span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt; tab-stops: 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">na</span></span></span></span></p>',	2,	4,	'2012-03-30 22:29:27',	4,	'2012-04-04 08:36:15'),
(33,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-04-06',	'<p>Spent most of the week editing the Integrated Lifecycle Management framework (formerly known as the SLM).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Did an edit/comment on the newly&nbsp;rewritten&nbsp;Configuration Management document circulated by IRM Governance/Info Quality group.&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>Captured all of the acronyms, did some rewriting,&nbsp;got&nbsp;almost&nbsp;to the end of the ILM document-haven\'t edited the glossary yet. Now time to start nailing down open questions (130+ \"comments\").</p>\r\n<p>Delivered 60+&nbsp;lines of comments on the CM doc, on the required Excel spreadsheet, on time per the deadline.</p>',	'<p>Met with Mr. Samuels to make sure I was heading in the direction he wanted for the (former)SLM.&nbsp; We are apparently in violent agreement.&nbsp; Time to start meeting with reps from other divisions to start integrating their thoughts (and answer my questions).</p>\r\n<p>Met briefly with Al\' Tariq and Christine Hawinson regarding some assistance she requires on a couple of Data Quality efforts.&nbsp; Needs assistance in putting together policies/procedures for funneling data calls through BTA to reduce the load on NOC; and in compiling a report (regarding information quality, the data for which has to come from the NOC).&nbsp; More to come next week.</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-04-06 15:39:10',	4,	'2012-04-10 17:29:35'),
(34,	12,	2,	1,	'2012-04-06',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Enterprise Architecture</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">On Monday, April 2<sup>nd</sup> I began a systematic review of the FEA Consolidated Reference Model as requested by Patrick Stingley.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>The FEA Consolidated Reference Model outlines and explains the Performance, Business, Service and Technical Reference Models that guide IT development activities of all federal agencies including the Bureau of Land Management. The intent of this review was to discuss the document with Patrick during the week of April 9-13 and begin to define what is needed.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">On the afternoon of Tuesday, April 3<sup>rd</sup> Al&rsquo;Tariq mentioned to me and Mohammad three activities related to Enterprise Architecture: EA itself, PMO and IT Service Operations. Mohammad was asked to lead this activity by Al&rsquo;Tariq.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>We agreed to conduct meetings to define roles, responsibilities, and specific deliverables.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">The following day, </span>Wednesday, April 4<sup>th</sup> Mohammad and I had a meeting to summarize what we thought were the requirements of each project.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I discovered from Mohammad that the BLM EA Framework developments is at the beginning stages, and the work done to date has led to the development of PMO templates for standardizing project reporting. I recommended that we outline how EA projects would be executed, and made several notations on a white-board.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>On Wednesday, <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">I reviewed several sources to capture WO-570; expressed intent for a PMO which could either be<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>i) a Program Management Office<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>or either<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>ii) a Project Management Office.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>I have concluded that WO-570 should do two things; 1) define how it should both establish a permanent Project Management Office that is responsible for implementation and proper use of project management methodology across BLM, as well as 2) recommend how the WO&rsquo;s can&nbsp;be assisted to create disciplined Program Management Office(s) focused on grouping projects that are aligned and achieve a common business objective.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>The following are aspects of a PMO that WO-570 must engage.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"line-height: normal; text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-add-space: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">o</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">List existing and new technologies </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"line-height: normal; text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-add-space: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">o</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Review current business processes and lay out a strategy of redesign</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"line-height: normal; text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-add-space: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">o</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Understand what new products or service offerings BLM wishes to develop</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"line-height: normal; text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-add-space: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">o</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Capture the list of all projects</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"line-height: normal; text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-add-space: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">o</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Define how current projects may be interrelated through technology, and common business objectives</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"line-height: normal; text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-add-space: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">o</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Define projects within the various functional boundaries of BLM </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"line-height: normal; text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-add-space: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">o</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Introduce traditional project management capabilities and methods </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">On Thursday, April 5<sup>th</sup> I defined the following EA project strawman to present to Mohammad and Patrick for their consideration. This strawman demonstrates how specific tasks to be performed will achieve goals listed in a charter that Mohammad is responsible for capturing.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Mohammad asked that I also begin to document for him what information from the DoDAF I thought would be useful for BLM.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>In brief, the DoDAF is a mature architecture framework&nbsp; based on operational, system, and technical views that guides how data is acquired to make decisions about how projects are implemented.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">On Friday, April 6<sup>th</sup> I continued to review the FEA Consolidated Reference Model.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I also began to&nbsp;identify a list of service elements of a Service Catalog with respect to IT Service Operations and have listed them below.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"NormalBulleted\" style=\"margin: 6pt 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span class=\"StyleFranklinGothicMedium10pt\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class=\"StyleFranklinGothicMedium10pt\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span>IT Services. </span></strong></span><span class=\"StyleFranklinGothicMedium10pt\"><em style=\"mso-bidi-font-style: normal;\"><span>A service provided to one or more Customers by an IT Service Provider. An IT Service is based on the use of Information Technology and supports the Customer&rsquo;s Business Processes. An IT Service is made up from a combination of People, Process and Technology and should be defined in a Service Level Agreement</span></em></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"NormalBulleted\" style=\"margin: 6pt 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span class=\"StyleFranklinGothicMedium10pt\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class=\"StyleFranklinGothicMedium10pt\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span>Business Services. </span></strong></span><span class=\"StyleFranklinGothicMedium10pt\"><em style=\"mso-bidi-font-style: normal;\"><span>An IT Service that directly supports a Business Process, as opposed to an Infrastructure Service, which is used internally by the IT Service Provider and is not usually visible to the Business</span></em></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"NormalBulleted\" style=\"margin: 6pt 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span class=\"StyleFranklinGothicMedium10pt\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span class=\"StyleFranklinGothicMedium10pt\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span>Infrastructure Services. </span></strong></span><span class=\"StyleFranklinGothicMedium10pt\"><em style=\"mso-bidi-font-style: normal;\"><span>An IT Service that is not directly used by the Business, but is required by the IT Service Provider so they can provide other IT Services. For example directory services, naming services, or communication services.</span></em></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Optimized GIS Mission Needs Statement </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">I am continuing to work on a Mission Needs Statement to develop a high performance or optimized Geospatial Information System (GIS). I have reviewed&nbsp;web literature (per Patrick)&nbsp;on render farm architecture.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Next steps are to conduct discussions on render farms with render farm companies, and evaluate specific features of render farms that will be appropriate for BLM systems. As stated in the previous weekly report, the goal is that WO-570 develop a high level architecture that will be successfully implemented by BLM personnel at the Network Operations Center.&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">The BLM MNS includes the following; impact on BLM mission areas, needed capability, current and planned capability, impact of not approving mission need benefits, timeframe, criticality, and long-range resource planning estimate.</span></span></span></span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Enterprise Architecture</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Thursday, April 5<sup>th</sup> </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align