(36,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-04-20',	'<p><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: black; font-size: 7.5pt;\">Translated the generic project schedule into the phases of the ILM and tracked deliverables to ensure that \"initial\" forms ultimately become either \"Updates\" or Finals.&nbsp; The main ILM graphic is nearly complete and reflects the actual process outlined by the CTO.&nbsp; Once finalized I will circulate within 570 for comment, and begin writing narrative to match the graphic and schedule.</span></p>',	'<p><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: black; font-size: 7.5pt;\">Managing to blend a formal but&nbsp;realistic system development schedule with the philosophy of&nbsp;an Integrated Lifecycle Managment framework and marry that with the precepts of CPIC&nbsp;is a significant accomplishment, at least in my mind.</span></p>',	'<p><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: black; font-size: 7.5pt;\">Spent considerable time with CTO, polishing the Generic development schedule and fitting it into the ILM framework.</span></p>',	'<p>None</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-04-16 09:13:09',	13,	'2012-04-30 15:11:54'),
(37,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-04-13',	'<p>Spent considerable time polishing a step-by-step software development schedule developed by CTO, which he feels should form the basis of the Integrated Lifecycle Management framework (I do not disagree).</p>\r\n<p>Continued editing/conceptualizing the ILM.</p>',	'<p>Completed the step-by-step SD schedule.</p>',	'<p>Spent a long meeting with CTO reviewing/refining the step-by-step schedule.</p>',	'<p>None</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-04-16 09:31:10',	4,	'2012-04-24 10:07:53'),
(40,	12,	2,	1,	'2012-04-20',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">I have provided an updated enterprise architecture task list to Mohammad for his review and feedback during weekly discussions.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>The goal of the plan is to offer best practice methodology and address specific BLM needs that lead to successful planning, implementation and maintenance of an enterprise architecture that is also well respected across the entire BLM organization.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>In addition to the plan, the following guidance was given to Mohammad as to how WO-570 may create an environment that will be receptive to WO-570&rsquo;s EA and PMO activities. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\">-</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">disseminate a EA Vision Statement and charter that has full support from BLM executive staff</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\">-</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">identify business unit stakeholders (e.g. division chiefs, state, district, center, and field office representatives)</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\">-</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">conduct a well-mapped campaign to explain what an EA needs to look like in terms of its relationship to an integrated life cycle framework, and Capital Planning and Investment Control (CPIC) process.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\">-</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">ask the business unit to promote buy-in so every area within BLM understands how it can contribute to the EA project plan.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\">-</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">defines a process to capture all business unit needs beyond existing or current functions.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">I think this is where CPIC should be used</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\">-</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">evaluate existing functions which are part of the \"As-Is\" architecture in all areas of BLM consistent with the FEA Business Reference Model that has defined measurement areas, and sub-categories (lines of business), and measurement groupings and indicators for all federal agencies.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\">-</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">understand the rationale for the \"As-Is&rdquo; architecture from the perspective of the states, districts, <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">and the bureau-wide centers.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Mohammad acknowledged that the EA task list provides the baseline for him to create and manage the project plan that includes tasks, as well as task durations and assigned resources. We discussed several examples of documentation typically used to identify and reflect an understanding of stakeholder needs (e.g. Initial Capability Documents, Performance Specifications, Topology Diagrams, and Interface Diagrams).<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>This type of discussion will need to continue as BLM overall has not emphasized usage of requirements documentation on its IT investments.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I am reviewing various technologies that are used within BLM and am seeking to understand areas of business or technical performance overlap or functional gaps.&nbsp; This includes a GIS render farm that was mentioned in earlier weekly reports.</span></span></span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Enterprise Architecture</span> - I updated the EA task list and reviewed the Diplomatic Security (DS) Enterprise Architecture that may be useful to BLM in making decisions about business and technical content that must be tracked within BLM as part of its current and future state.&nbsp;&nbsp; P. Stingley provided the disk with a version of the DS Enterprise Architecture.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">PMO</span> - Since Mohammad indicated that he intends to share ideas with me about the PMO structure and policy related matters, I compiled a summary of the requirements that the EA project should adhere to in accordance with best project management methodology</span></span></span></p>\r\n<ol type=\"1\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt; color: black; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Project Charter</span></span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt; color: black; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Project Scope Statement</span></span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt; color: black; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; tab-stops: list .5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Project Management Plan. Note that a project plan or schedule in MS Project is just one section of the bigger Project Management Plan.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>The overall Project Management Plan has the following components; </span></span><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Scope Management Plan, </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Schedule Management Plan, </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Cost Management Plan, </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Quality Management Plan, </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Staffing Management Plan, </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Communication Management Plan, </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Risk Management Plan, </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Procurement Management Plan</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">A plan for Integration Management (a project management knowledge area) is not specified.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>To manage projects effectively, the project should be divided into phases and the smallest possible sub-phases. The iterative process should go all the way down to the level where further division would create chaos rather than actually helping the project.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>The five stages of project management (i.e. initiation, planning, execution, monitoring and control, and closing) are subdivided into processes as shown below (PMBOK 4th Edition: Process Chart).</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<table class=\"MsoNormalTable\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; mso-border-alt: solid #070707 .75pt; mso-yfti-tbllook: 1184; mso-padding-alt: 1.2pt 1.2pt 1.2pt 1.2pt;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow: 0; mso-yfti-firstrow: yes;\">\r\n<td style=\"background: #e6f5d5; mso-border-alt: inset #070707 .75pt; border: #070707 1pt inset; padding: 1.2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"border-bottom: #070707 1pt inset; border-left: #f0f0f0; background: #e6f5d5; border-top: #070707 1pt inset; border-right: #070707 1pt inset; mso-border-alt: inset #070707 .75pt; mso-border-left-alt: inset #070707 .75pt; padding: 1.2pt;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 7.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Initiation</span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border-bottom: #070707 1pt inset; border-left: #f0f0f0; background: #e6f5d5; border-top: #070707 1pt inset; border-right: #070707 1pt inset; mso-border-alt: inset #070707 .75pt; mso-border-left-alt: inset #070707 .75pt; padding: 1.2pt;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 7.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Planning</span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border-bottom: #070707 1pt inset; border-left: #f0f0f0; background: #e6f5d5; border-top: #070707 1pt inset; border-right: #070707 1pt inset; mso-border-alt: inset #070707 .75pt; mso-border-left-alt: inset #070707 .75pt; padding: 1.2pt;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 7.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Executing</span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border-bottom: #070707 1pt inset; border-left: #f0f0f0; background: #e6f5d5; border-top: #070707 1pt inset; border-right: #070707 1pt inset; mso-border-alt: inset #070707 .75pt; mso-border-left-alt: inset #070707 .75pt; padding: 1.2pt;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 7.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Monitoring and Controlling</span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border-bottom: #070707 1pt inset; border-left: #f0f0f0; background: #e6f5d5; border-top: #070707 1pt inset; border-right: #070707 1pt inset; mso-border-alt: inset #070707 .75pt; mso-border-left-alt: inset #070707 .75pt; padding: 1.2pt;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 7.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Closing</span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow: 1;\">\r\n<td style=\"border-bottom: #070707 1pt inset; border-left: #070707 1pt inset; background: white; border-top: #f0f0f0; border-right: #070707 1pt inset; mso-border-alt: inset #070707 .75pt; mso-border-top-alt: inset #070707 .75pt; padding: 1.2pt;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 7.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Integration<br /><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\" /><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\" /></span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border-bottom: #070707 1pt inset; border-left: #f0f0f0; background: white; border-top: #f0f0f0; border-right: #070707 1pt inset; mso-border-alt: inset #070707 .75pt; mso-border-left-alt: inset #070707 .75pt; mso-border-top-alt: inset #070707 .75pt; padding: 1.2pt;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" sty