(92,	16,	2,	1,	'2012-09-07',	'<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">For Mission Critical Business (MCB) project, I have analyzed new data for Mission Critical Business (MCB) application per request from BLM team to kick start the core team meeting.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Also met with Dario, Naomi, Marcos and Chris to discuss next steps.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Team liked so far what I have done and they suggested to show the same data to the core team and ask for their input.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">In order to find some analyzing tool for MCB project data, I researched some online tool which can help analyze MCB data project.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>We are going ask for some suggestion for the tool when we meet with the core team in next week or so.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">I am continuing to add more sections for the federal mobility document.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I am just following Federal Mobility Strategy outline.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">Mission Critical Business Project &ndash; Finished initial analysis of the snapshot.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Will need to do this analysis again when the data call is finished.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">Federal Mobility Strategy &ndash; Written few parts of the strategy.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">Lead an initial meeting (Teleconference with Dario, Chris, Marcos and Naomi) to discuss future plan for the Mission Critical Business (MCB) project meeting.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Showed analysis and discussed what&rsquo;s next step.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Will have more direction when we meet with Core team sometime next week.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">Had a conference call with Dario and Chris to have a brainstorming session for cleanup efforts for the MCB data collection.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">Met with Naomi and Al&rsquo;Tariq to check status of each state\'s status on MCB data collection.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">n/a</span></p>',	'<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">n/a</span></p>',	2,	4,	'2012-09-07 11:31:52',	16,	'2012-09-11 16:46:51'),
(93,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-09-07',	'<p>Four day week after Labor Day holiday. Ground out the final yards&nbsp;in preparation&nbsp;for delivery of&nbsp;the 2012 FDCCI Project Plan.&nbsp; Due date Friday,&nbsp;9/7; final edits from NOC&nbsp;completed that morning, hand-delivered by Mr. Stingley to signers @ MIB,&nbsp; Pat wrote plan copy, I handled assembly, analysis &amp; insertion&nbsp;of TCO documents, development a BLM cost model, produced analysis of closure effects similar to the intent of the TCO model, but accurate for BLM under a defined set of assumptions.&nbsp; Finalized schedule of closings and built plan in MS Project.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>BLM is scheduled to close 47 data centers by 12/31/14, out of a total of 105 for all of DOI. Numerous challenges remain, in particular,&nbsp;lack of a&nbsp;cloud contract makes it almost impossible to plan how the closures will actually be performed.&nbsp; Cloud Contract now scheduled for December at the earliest.&nbsp; New Plan calls for a six-month hiatus for site&nbsp;closures, while several planning efforts are addressed (GIS architecture, NOC Storage, Plan for move to NOC if Cloud does not offer&nbsp;services necessary. Follow on 3 months are analysis and planning for the cloud move, restarting closures in 3Q 2013, total of 8 sites in the year.</p>',	'<p>Completed BLM 2012 FDCCI master plan.&nbsp; Electronic version delivered to project office Friday AM was first in of all BLM Bureaus. (Must be formally&nbsp;signed by ADIRM.)</p>\r\n<p>Sent notes to FDCCI Project Office on deficiencies in TCO model; latest draft is considerably improved, (now reports correct # of BLM closures)&nbsp;but still has arithmetic problems. E.g. forecast of electricity usage savings in KWh seem reasonable; but at $0.1029 national average per KWh, a savings of $210K on 1.9M KWh&nbsp;is reported as around $30K (around $0.015) FI, latest TCO draft delivered Thursday for inclusion in plan due Friday.</p>',	'<p>Telecons with DOI FDCCI&nbsp;Project Office and NOC regarding Plan and September Closures (6 more Oregon sites due by 9/28). Documents are all prepped (by me, in July)&nbsp;and ready for signoff by SIRMO.</p>',	'<p>Concerns over funding support for NOC for FDCCI.&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-09-07 12:13:19',	4,	'2012-09-11 16:51:13'),
