(102,	16,	2,	1,	'2012-09-28',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">For Mission Critical Business (MCB) project, I had created a presentation based on our last week&rsquo;s discussion about data clean up meeting.&nbsp; I also created a mockup chart to show it to the core team and get their feedback.&nbsp; We will get more information about objectives in next week&rsquo;s meeting.&nbsp; I also met with Dario from New Mexico face to face to get a little more background </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Based on the new assignment of Portfolio management, I have started to review the documentation regarding these projects.&nbsp; I have also gained access to EDMS so I can look at the old documentation.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">I have also started to work on Vendor selection/evaluation process flowchart per request from Mohammad.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Mission Critical Business (MCB) Project &ndash; Created a presentation for core team with data cleanup team summary and mockup charts.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Reviewed ITIB presentation for ESRS and SPATS system to get understanding of the current status.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Started to map process for the vendor selection/evaluation.</span></p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Data cleanup discussion meeting &ndash; Sent out presentation to data cleanup team and had face to face discussion with Dario Lunardi from New Mexico.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Attended a staff meeting of WO-570 to discuss and give update on current project status.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-09-28 14:09:45',	4,	'2012-10-08 18:14:26'),
(103,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-09-28',	'<p>Received new project assignments last Friday, additional projects Tuesday.&nbsp; I am now responsible for six legacy systems: ALIS, the Alaska Land Information System; BASS, the BLM Automated Security System; CARS, the Cadastral Automated Response System;GLO, the General Land Office Records System, ITAMS (about which I am currently searching for&nbsp;information), and LR2000, the Legacy Rehosting of some 9 applications at the turn of the Millenium.&nbsp; Finding information on these applications is dicey; searching for an up to date centralized repository (although we have been given 3-4 websites where information should reside.).</p>\r\n<p>Spent some time trying to assist the FDCCI PM in Denver in arriving at a strategy for running ADAT surveys.&nbsp; There is a strong desire to limit the workload placed on the states, but the Department has a strong desire to have useful surveys performed and they will be extremely useful for Enterprise Architecture.&nbsp; For example, they were planning to&nbsp; bundle applications from a dozen companies as \"GIS\".&nbsp; My recommendation was to do it by license.&nbsp; The Microsoft Office license covers&nbsp; Excel, Powerpoint, Word, etc., so that represents a bundle...but Visio would have to be ADAT\'d separately.&nbsp; Checked with Mr. Stingley and he concurred; PM undecided.</p>\r\n<p>Took/Passed FISSA+ training requirement.</p>',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Shipped the final six FDCCI Closure Documents for Oregon to the Department, signed by ADIR, bringing the total for the fiscal year to 15 closures.</p>\r\n<p>Spent some time working with FDCCI PM on a strategy for ADAT surveys.&nbsp; Strong desire to limit the effort by State personnel by bundling wherever possible.&nbsp; Advised that bundling software from a dozen vendors and calling it \"GIS\" was not going to be acceptable to CTO, probably not useful for the purposes for which&nbsp;ADAT was dictated by DOI\'s CIO.&nbsp; Suggested dividing by license: Do one survey for Microsoft Office (one license), don\'t survey Excel, Word, PowerPoint, etc.&nbsp; But do survey Visio, Project, separate Office products with standalone licenses.&nbsp; Check, Mr. Stingley concurred; PM considering.</p>',	'<p>Produced a short presentation on the status of the ILM for the Information Resources Management Team.&nbsp; Reached consensus on several minor changes to the document, but more meetings are necessary to carve out definitive&nbsp;roles and responsibilities.&nbsp; Strong CPIC push for calling PM\'s \"Investment Managers\".&nbsp; Lively discussion, good points offered, food for thought.</p>\r\n<p>Met with NOC/570 team working on the ILM as well.&nbsp;&nbsp;NOC co-lead (with Ms. Bowers) did not attend, so only a bit of&nbsp;progress, regarding project number assignments, and discussion about interfacing the new PPM tool with the existing time sheet system&nbsp;(PPM contract&nbsp;was awarded and was to be in place in a&nbsp;few weeks...but now the award has been&nbsp;protested, so now&nbsp;it wil be an indefinite time&nbsp;longer.)&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Weekly FDCCI call did not raise any burning issues; we were advised that the TCO model is not going away, so prepare to help make it work.</p>\r\n<p>Biweekly staff meeting was interesting; announcement that Mr. Stingley and Mr. Smith will be TDY\'d to WO580 to help address a gap.&nbsp; Also announced two four hour planning meetings for week after next.</p>',	'<p>None</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-09-28 16:43:35',	4,	'2012-10-08 18:11:45'),
