(124,	51,	'Update: As of 10/17 Phase 1 was completed - Letter of Notification of Intent to Change Address was sent to Contracting Officer - awaiting formal response.  Working on phase 2 Dun & Bradstreet process for updating in their system.',	NULL,	NULL,	11,	'2012-10-24 09:16:15'),
(125,	54,	'Update: Initial contact made with D&B representative: Information in order to access website to update our company listing was received 10/17.  Awaiting corp exec information needed to register for security access to iUpdate.\r\n\r\nInfo listed on step by step process to register with iUpdate:\r\n\r\nStep 1 - Company look-up (I have this info)\r\n\r\nStep 2 \r\n1.  Legal name  - as appears on drivers license \r\n2.  Home telephone \r\n3.  current physical home address\r\n\r\nStep 3 - Authentication Exam - (personal information) will not know what will be asked, so  will followup when prompted on questionnaire.\r\n',	NULL,	NULL,	11,	'2012-10-24 09:28:39'),
(126,	56,	'Update:\r\n\r\nOnce procedure for working on this task was received, I coordinated with Mr. Springfield on process we would follow to accomplish this task on 10/18.  I retrieved from the corporate folder the four (4) resumes  - formatted drafts of each and emailed same to Mr. Springfield for review on 10/19 - followed up mid day with note checking on status - received response that drafts resumes were received and that he was still reviewing.\r\nOn 10/22 checked on status - no response\r\nOn 10/23 checked on status - no response\r\nAs of 10/24 I am still awaiting a response as to whether the resumes require edits or as presented are acceptable to upload to the corporate folder - in order for me to mark this task as completed.\r\n\r\nThank you, Ella',	NULL,	NULL,	11,	'2012-10-24 09:41:03'),
(127,	58,	'Robert/Moneeka,\r\n\r\nPlease coordinate the interviews.  Perhaps we can get Laverne Norcome and Darlene Williams-Prades in on Friday.  Maybe the others later in the week...next week.  If not, we can do them all later next week.  I like what Laverne Norcome (on paper)  brings to the table; definetly in line with Atechra\\\'s DVI program.  Darlene Williams-Prades scares me; she has the education and experience, however, one of two things are happening here (1) as she states, \\\"needs a job, so being picky isn\\\'t an option; therefore, I would not have any expectations that she would be with us long; so, I would be hestiate in hiring or (2) something is hidden here, why vest years and money to receive an MBA to work as an admin asst?  Things that make you...no me, go hmmmm.',	NULL,	NULL,	2,	'2012-10-31 13:46:27');
